        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 5:33PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 533 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of strong
thunderstorms extending from near Log Lane Village to over
Westplains, or extending from near Fort Morgan to 23 miles northwest
of Sterling, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sterling, Fort Morgan, Brush, Log Lane Village, Merino, Hillrose,
Willard, Pawnee Pass, Snyder, Prewitt Reservoir, Antelope Springs,
Stoneham, Logan Corners, Atwood, Midway, Messex, Union and Fort
Morgan Airport.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
